definitions.definition: The middle of the night : the sixth temporal hour , equidistant between sunset and sunrise .
examples: Thanks to its sonar, the narwhal can remain active even at midnight , unhindered by the darkness.

definitions.definition: Synonym of boxcars ( “ a pair of sixes ” ) .

main_definition: The middle of the night : the sixth temporal hour , equidistant between sunset and sunrise .
secondary_definitions: ( dice games ) Synonym of boxcars ( “ a pair of sixes ” ) .
